--- Barabási-Albert (BA) Model Results ---

Hardware Efficiency:
- Max Memory (VRAM): 8534 MB
- Batch Processing Time: ~0.62 seconds/batch

Final Training Metrics (Epoch 10):
- Acc@1: 78.57%
- Acc@5: 98.88%
- Loss: 0.616

Notes: 
- The BA "Rich-Get-Richer" hub network performed slightly better than the purely random ER/GNM models, but still fell short of the highly-clustered WS baseline.
- Like ER/GNM, it still requires massive memory (8534 MB) to process due to long-range hub connections, proving again that small-world topologies are the most efficient for SNNs.
